1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,794
[MARISTELLA] <i>I also want to thank you.</i>

2
00:00:02,877 --> 00:00:06,589
<i>I talked to Macky,</i>
<i>and he said you helped save him.</i>

3
00:00:06,673 --> 00:00:10,802
<i>I promise you that you and your family</i>
<i>will be well compensated.</i>

4
00:00:10,885 --> 00:00:12,971
<i>I'm not asking for compensation.</i>

5
00:00:13,054 --> 00:00:14,055
<i>I only want one thing.</i>

6
00:00:14,139 --> 00:00:15,223
<i>Justice.</i>

7
00:00:15,306 --> 00:00:16,599
<i>For my grandpa,</i>

8
00:00:16,683 --> 00:00:19,185
<i>and for all the innocent people</i>
<i>who lost their lives.</i>

9
00:00:19,853 --> 00:00:22,731
<i>Mama's just suspecting that</i>
<i>Papa is Olsen's father.</i>

10
00:00:23,314 --> 00:00:28,069
<i>But she also says that</i>
<i>Papa still loves Auntie Wendy.</i>

11
00:00:28,153 --> 00:00:29,112
<i>I mean, seriously?</i>

12
00:00:29,195 --> 00:00:30,905
<i>You saw what happened on the island.</i>

13
00:00:30,989 --> 00:00:33,074
<i>Isn't that enough proof?</i>

14
00:00:33,158 --> 00:00:35,326
<i>He never abandoned your mother.</i>

15
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:36,828
<i>That's love, dude.</i>

16
00:00:36,911 --> 00:00:38,246
<i>That's love.</i>

17
00:00:38,830 --> 00:00:39,914
<i>Just admit it.</i>

18
00:00:39,998 --> 00:00:42,333
<i>It's possible that Olsen is your son.</i>

19
00:00:43,251 --> 00:00:48,131
<i>We had an agreement</i>
<i>after what happened.</i>

20
00:00:48,214 --> 00:00:52,260
<i>No one can ever come between us again.</i>

21
00:00:52,927 --> 00:00:53,970
<i>No one.</i>

22
00:00:54,054 --> 00:00:58,349
<i>Because no matter what happens,</i>
<i>we love each other.</i>

23
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:01,019
<i>Lucas, I'm nervous.</i>

24
00:01:01,102 --> 00:01:02,896
<i>There's no turning back now.</i>

25
00:01:02,979 --> 00:01:07,192
<i>Our priority is to extract Leni</i>
<i>before we attack.</i>

26
00:01:07,275 --> 00:01:08,568
<i>What attack?</i>

27
00:01:08,651 --> 00:01:13,198
<i>Mila, all of the money</i>
<i>and jewelry is missing.</i>

28
00:01:13,281 --> 00:01:17,410
<i>Only Jacinto knows where everything went.</i>

29
00:01:17,494 --> 00:01:19,496
<i>That's why we had you look for him.</i>

30
00:01:20,747 --> 00:01:22,040
- [HANDCUFFS RATTLE]
- [GROANS]

31
00:01:25,376 --> 00:01:28,421
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

32
00:01:29,339 --> 00:01:35,136
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

33
00:01:55,532 --> 00:01:57,033
Our relievers aren't here yet.

34
00:01:57,117 --> 00:01:59,077
- They're running late.
- What time will they come?

35
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,829
I'm getting hungry now.

36
00:02:00,912 --> 00:02:03,748
There's no one to relieve us
from our post.

37
00:02:03,832 --> 00:02:05,917
- Our shift should've ended now.
- I know, right?

38
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,169
What's taking them so long?
Look at the time.

39
00:02:08,253 --> 00:02:10,004
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

40
00:02:10,088 --> 00:02:11,714
Good evening, Doc.

41
00:02:11,798 --> 00:02:14,217
May we see your ID?

42
00:02:15,510 --> 00:02:16,511
Good evening.

43
00:02:16,594 --> 00:02:17,804
[COP] I'm sorry, Doc.

44
00:02:17,887 --> 00:02:19,139
We just need it for verification

45
00:02:19,222 --> 00:02:21,141
since access to the patient is restricted.

46
00:02:25,854 --> 00:02:31,025
[MUSIC BECOMES TENSE]

47
00:02:31,943 --> 00:02:33,069
[MILA] Uh…

48
00:02:33,987 --> 00:02:35,196
Sir.

49
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:39,159
Sir, we need access
to the patient in Room 209

50
00:02:39,242 --> 00:02:42,036
because she has to be sent to the OR.

51
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:43,788
It's really urgent.

52
00:02:43,872 --> 00:02:48,293
And I was informed that
the patient has internal bleeding.

53
00:02:49,210 --> 00:02:50,670
We can't afford any delays.

54
00:02:50,753 --> 00:02:56,426
And I promised your superior
that I would take care of her.

55
00:02:56,509 --> 00:02:58,636
I cannot let her die.

56
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:03,933
I'm fully aware that she is a key person
of the La Playa Roja siege.

57
00:03:04,017 --> 00:03:08,730
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

58
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:24,037
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

59
00:03:55,443 --> 00:04:01,908
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

60
00:04:18,132 --> 00:04:23,846
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

61
00:04:51,332 --> 00:04:53,042
[ROMAN] Get your act together.

62
00:04:54,836 --> 00:04:56,170
Wait, hold on.

63
00:04:56,254 --> 00:04:57,338
Who's that?

64
00:04:58,047 --> 00:05:00,466
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [MILA STAMMERS] It's Leni Padua.

65
00:05:01,634 --> 00:05:02,593
Let me check.

66
00:05:08,766 --> 00:05:10,268
It really is Leni Padua.

67
00:05:11,269 --> 00:05:14,522
The doctor said we already have
clearance to take her.

68
00:05:16,024 --> 00:05:17,191
Okay.

69
00:05:23,239 --> 00:05:24,907
Hello, Nurse Mafe.

70
00:05:25,658 --> 00:05:27,160
Any update about the CT scan?

71
00:05:27,243 --> 00:05:28,411
[LIAM] Don't sleep.

72
00:05:28,494 --> 00:05:30,330
[LUNA] I'm not sleeping.

73
00:05:30,413 --> 00:05:32,123
All right. Thank you.

74
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:36,252
[LIAM] Dude.

75
00:05:36,878 --> 00:05:37,712
- Luna.
- Doc.

76
00:05:37,795 --> 00:05:40,256
Let's do a quick CT scan.
Follow me.

77
00:05:40,339 --> 00:05:42,091
Oh, I'm okay, Doc.

78
00:05:42,175 --> 00:05:43,468
No need for that.

79
00:05:43,551 --> 00:05:44,844
I can manage.

80
00:05:44,927 --> 00:05:45,970
There you go again.

81
00:05:46,054 --> 00:05:48,431
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

82
00:05:50,308 --> 00:05:52,935
Liam, this is Doc Ivan, by the way.

83
00:05:56,397 --> 00:05:58,941
Doc, does my friend
have to be admitted here?

84
00:05:59,609 --> 00:06:01,944
- I already said no.
- Let's listen to him first.

85
00:06:02,612 --> 00:06:03,988
- I'm okay now.
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

86
00:06:04,072 --> 00:06:04,906
[IVAN] Come on.

87
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:07,116
- Dude.
- But, Doc--

88
00:06:09,744 --> 00:06:11,079
Let's go.

89
00:06:11,662 --> 00:06:15,291
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

90
00:06:16,667 --> 00:06:19,337
- [SIGHS] Dude…
- Let's go with him. Come on.

91
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:26,594
[IVAN] Doc.

92
00:06:28,721 --> 00:06:29,597
- Doc?
- [LUNA] Sorry.

93
00:06:31,724 --> 00:06:33,309
[LIAM] It's okay.

94
00:06:35,061 --> 00:06:41,692
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

95
00:06:52,245 --> 00:06:58,292
[TENSE MUSIC RISES]

96
00:07:05,591 --> 00:07:08,219
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

97
00:07:08,302 --> 00:07:09,929
Ma'am.

98
00:07:10,721 --> 00:07:11,639
[SIGHS]

99
00:07:11,722 --> 00:07:13,307
No matter how many times
I try to compute this,

100
00:07:13,391 --> 00:07:15,518
our bill is really 50,000.

101
00:07:17,228 --> 00:07:18,896
[SIGHS]

102
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:21,274
Since Ma'am Greta is also here,

103
00:07:21,357 --> 00:07:24,652
maybe we can ask her for a cash advance
or to lend us some money.

104
00:07:24,735 --> 00:07:26,112
Seriously?

105
00:07:26,195 --> 00:07:29,407
You want to borrow money
from someone who got traumatized?

106
00:07:29,490 --> 00:07:30,533
Tsk.

107
00:07:30,616 --> 00:07:33,578
But, ma'am, we also
got traumatized, right?

108
00:07:33,661 --> 00:07:34,912
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

109
00:07:34,996 --> 00:07:38,583
And this bill just added to that trauma.

110
00:07:40,168 --> 00:07:41,627
Tsk.

111
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:45,381
We should've been out yesterday,

112
00:07:45,465 --> 00:07:47,508
but the doctors were too much

113
00:07:47,592 --> 00:07:51,471
with all these checkups and lab tests.

114
00:07:51,554 --> 00:07:53,681
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

115
00:07:53,764 --> 00:07:56,684
Ma'am, I have a plan.

116
00:07:56,767 --> 00:07:57,810
What is it?

117
00:07:57,894 --> 00:07:59,687
[WHISPERS] Let's just run away.

118
00:07:59,770 --> 00:08:02,982
You know, you think like a criminal.

119
00:08:03,774 --> 00:08:06,110
Well, I don't want to
be taken hostage again.

120
00:08:06,194 --> 00:08:08,613
This bill will take us hostage here.

121
00:08:09,363 --> 00:08:11,782
[HUFFS] We might end up living here.

122
00:08:12,450 --> 00:08:16,996
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

123
00:08:17,079 --> 00:08:18,456
[SIGHS]

124
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:25,630
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [MILA] Come on. Let's just go this way.

125
00:08:26,214 --> 00:08:27,798
We need to bring her to the OR right away.

126
00:08:28,799 --> 00:08:35,348
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

127
00:08:37,183 --> 00:08:38,017
[LUNA] Dude.

128
00:08:39,435 --> 00:08:40,353
Liam!

129
00:08:42,104 --> 00:08:42,939
Dude.

130
00:08:43,022 --> 00:08:44,273
Dude!

131
00:08:44,357 --> 00:08:46,526
I have to do something.
Please take care of her.

132
00:08:46,609 --> 00:08:48,528
- I'll be back!
- Liam!

133
00:08:48,611 --> 00:08:49,779
No.

134
00:08:50,905 --> 00:08:57,119
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

135
00:08:59,830 --> 00:09:01,249
[COP] Hold on.

136
00:09:02,124 --> 00:09:03,626
Why are you bringing her here?

137
00:09:04,627 --> 00:09:06,796
Sir, is the patient--

138
00:09:06,879 --> 00:09:08,798
- [MUFFLED GUNSHOTS]
- [BODIES THUD]

139
00:09:08,881 --> 00:09:12,176
[WHIMPERING, BREATHING HEAVILY]

140
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:15,763
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

141
00:09:15,846 --> 00:09:16,847
Come on!

142
00:09:17,431 --> 00:09:23,062
[WHIMPERING, BREATHING HEAVILY]

143
00:09:23,145 --> 00:09:24,564
[ROMAN] Take this off.

144
00:09:28,734 --> 00:09:30,444
[MILA KEEPS WHIMPERING]

145
00:09:31,737 --> 00:09:33,864
Come on! Go! Go! Go!

146
00:09:35,199 --> 00:09:37,076
- Come on, let's go!
- [WHIMPERS]

147
00:09:38,202 --> 00:09:39,328
Hurry up! Move!

148
00:09:39,412 --> 00:09:46,168
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

149
00:09:52,174 --> 00:09:53,301
[MUFFLED GUNSHOTS]

150
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:54,719
- [BODY THUDS]
- [GRUNTS]

151
00:09:59,348 --> 00:10:06,022
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

152
00:10:06,105 --> 00:10:07,565
[KICKS LIGHTLY]

153
00:10:10,568 --> 00:10:12,111
[FREDO GRUNTS]

154
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:17,533
- [KICK LANDS]
- [GRUNTS]

155
00:10:17,617 --> 00:10:21,078
- [GRUNTING]
- [BLOWS LANDING]

156
00:10:21,162 --> 00:10:23,372
- [SHOUTS]
- [BODY THUDS]

157
00:10:23,456 --> 00:10:25,916
- [BLOWS LANDING]
- [GRUNTING]

158
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,501
- [BODY THUDS]
- [GROANS]

159
00:10:27,585 --> 00:10:29,045
[GRUNTS]

160
00:10:29,128 --> 00:10:30,212
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [GROANS]

161
00:10:31,297 --> 00:10:34,925
- [GRUNTING]
- [BODY THUDS]

162
00:10:35,009 --> 00:10:35,968
[GROANS]

163
00:10:37,595 --> 00:10:39,555
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [GROANS]

164
00:10:39,639 --> 00:10:41,641
- [KICK LANDS]
- [GRUNTS]

165
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:42,808
[GRUNTS]

166
00:10:42,892 --> 00:10:44,727
- [BODY THUDS]
- [GROANS]

167
00:10:44,810 --> 00:10:46,187
- [KICK LANDS]
- [GRUNTS]

168
00:10:48,397 --> 00:10:50,775
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

169
00:11:01,077 --> 00:11:08,084
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

170
00:11:12,922 --> 00:11:17,510
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

171
00:11:17,593 --> 00:11:18,761
[GASPS]

172
00:11:19,887 --> 00:11:21,639
Let's go this way! Come on!

173
00:11:21,722 --> 00:11:28,562
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

174
00:11:32,108 --> 00:11:33,150
[GATE CLANKS]

175
00:11:34,610 --> 00:11:37,238
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

176
00:11:37,321 --> 00:11:38,864
- [ELEVATOR CREAKS]
- [MILA WHIMPERS]

177
00:11:53,587 --> 00:11:55,214
[METAL DOOR CLANKS]

178
00:11:56,048 --> 00:11:57,299
Hurry!

179
00:11:57,383 --> 00:11:58,926
[GATE CLANKS]

180
00:12:00,845 --> 00:12:02,054
[GRUNTS]

181
00:12:03,055 --> 00:12:04,348
[GATE CLANKS]

182
00:12:09,311 --> 00:12:16,277
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

183
00:12:17,528 --> 00:12:18,571
[PANTING]

184
00:12:20,948 --> 00:12:23,117
Where are the nurse and the doctor
who were with the patient?

185
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,201
Why?

186
00:12:25,244 --> 00:12:26,829
- Call the police and security!
- Why?

187
00:12:26,912 --> 00:12:28,956
- Why?
- Just tell them to follow!

188
00:12:29,039 --> 00:12:30,082
- But--
- Why, sir?

189
00:12:30,166 --> 00:12:31,333
- [GUN COCKS]
- Just do it!

190
00:12:31,417 --> 00:12:32,626
Oh my God!

191
00:12:33,794 --> 00:12:35,129
[WOMAN SQUEALS]

192
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:37,715
- [EMIL] Leni, dear!
- Papa!

193
00:12:37,798 --> 00:12:39,175
[LUCAS] Mila! Mila!

194
00:12:39,758 --> 00:12:41,135
[MILA SOBBING]

195
00:12:41,218 --> 00:12:42,344
- Mila, come here.
- Let's go.

196
00:12:42,428 --> 00:12:43,387
You need to leave now.

197
00:12:43,471 --> 00:12:44,889
[EMIL] I told you I'd come back for you.

198
00:12:44,972 --> 00:12:46,432
- You need to leave!
- I don't want to go.

199
00:12:46,515 --> 00:12:48,142
I won't leave without you!

200
00:12:48,225 --> 00:12:49,894
- Leave now!
- No.

201
00:12:49,977 --> 00:12:51,312
Get in there.

202
00:12:51,395 --> 00:12:52,897
If things turn messy, you'll be hurt.

203
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:55,816
[SOBBING] I'm not leaving without you.

204
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:57,860
[EMIL] Hold on, dear. That's it.

205
00:12:58,486 --> 00:12:59,570
All right.

206
00:12:59,653 --> 00:13:02,948
- Assist her.
- [MILA] I don't want to leave.

207
00:13:03,032 --> 00:13:05,117
I want us to stay together.

208
00:13:05,201 --> 00:13:07,286
Hey, where's Fredo?

209
00:13:08,412 --> 00:13:09,580
Someone saw us.

210
00:13:09,663 --> 00:13:11,123
He chased them.

211
00:13:14,668 --> 00:13:19,131
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

212
00:13:19,215 --> 00:13:21,592
Hurry up. We're out of time.

213
00:13:22,134 --> 00:13:24,553
If the person Fredo chased
alerts the police,

214
00:13:24,637 --> 00:13:25,721
we're done for.

215
00:13:25,804 --> 00:13:29,391
We need to get inside the hospital
before the police are alerted.

216
00:13:29,475 --> 00:13:30,392
Yes, sir.

217
00:13:30,476 --> 00:13:32,686
- [SECURITY] Hey, wait a sec!
- [GUNSHOTS]

218
00:13:34,063 --> 00:13:35,898
[MILA] Why did you shoot him?

219
00:13:35,981 --> 00:13:37,650
I can't bear this anymore.

220
00:13:37,733 --> 00:13:39,318
- Let's get out of here!
- [LUCAS] Mila… Mila!

221
00:13:39,401 --> 00:13:41,445
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

222
00:13:41,529 --> 00:13:43,781
I'm not leaving without the money.

223
00:13:43,864 --> 00:13:46,617
- We'll follow Boss Emil's plan.
- No.

224
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:49,203
Have you all lost your minds?

225
00:13:49,286 --> 00:13:52,581
Don't you know how many cops are here?

226
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:55,876
The police won't touch us
if we take people hostage.

227
00:13:55,960 --> 00:14:00,839
Once we capture the Rojas, the senator
and his son, and the whole hospital…

228
00:14:00,923 --> 00:14:02,925
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

229
00:14:03,008 --> 00:14:05,469
…we'll get everything we want!

230
00:14:05,553 --> 00:14:09,014
[SOBBING] Lucas, let's go.

231
00:14:09,098 --> 00:14:15,312
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

232
00:14:16,397 --> 00:14:17,982
- [ALARM BLARING]
- [GROANS]

233
00:14:18,607 --> 00:14:24,238
[ALARM BLARING]

234
00:14:33,914 --> 00:14:36,500
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

235
00:14:36,584 --> 00:14:39,712
Damn it! Go now, quick!

236
00:14:39,795 --> 00:14:42,464
- No! Lucas, I don't want to go!
- Go now!

237
00:14:42,548 --> 00:14:48,679
[ALARM BLARING]

238
00:14:48,762 --> 00:14:50,556
Where's Papa? Papa!

239
00:14:51,432 --> 00:14:53,809
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [SHOUTS]

240
00:14:56,395 --> 00:14:59,398
The fire alarm's gone off!
Is there a fire?

241
00:14:59,481 --> 00:15:02,234
- Maybe it's a fire drill.
- A fire drill? At this hour?

242
00:15:02,902 --> 00:15:06,989
[ALARM BLARING]

243
00:15:07,072 --> 00:15:14,079
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

244
00:15:18,584 --> 00:15:25,591
[MUSIC BECOMES SUSPENSEFUL]

245
00:15:29,762 --> 00:15:31,180
Leni.

246
00:15:31,263 --> 00:15:32,681
Leni, get back here!

247
00:15:32,765 --> 00:15:33,974
I need to talk to Papa.

248
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,894
- [MILA] Hey!
- [GWEN] Leni!

249
00:15:36,977 --> 00:15:39,188
Hey! Leni, where are you going?

250
00:15:39,271 --> 00:15:40,856
- Leni!
- Leni!

251
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:42,191
Let me out!

252
00:15:42,274 --> 00:15:44,443
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

253
00:15:44,526 --> 00:15:46,528
- Hey, Leni!
- Leni, come back!

254
00:15:47,363 --> 00:15:49,031
- [MILA] Hey, Leni.
- Leni, stop right there.

255
00:15:50,532 --> 00:15:51,700
Should we call the cops?

256
00:15:52,576 --> 00:15:54,870
Let's go! Let's go! Come on!

257
00:15:54,954 --> 00:16:01,043
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

258
00:16:02,044 --> 00:16:03,420
[STAFF] What's going on?

259
00:16:12,346 --> 00:16:13,681
I need to see Papa.

260
00:16:13,764 --> 00:16:15,724
- Your father will get angry.
- Leni.

261
00:16:16,308 --> 00:16:17,559
- Come on.
- I need to see Papa.

262
00:16:17,643 --> 00:16:19,186
We'll get you out of here.

263
00:16:19,269 --> 00:16:21,188
We worked so hard to get in here.

264
00:16:21,271 --> 00:16:23,524
- Come on, Leni. Please!
- Papa!

265
00:16:23,607 --> 00:16:26,652
Your father will get angry. Leni, please!

266
00:16:26,735 --> 00:16:27,736
Pa!

267
00:16:28,570 --> 00:16:30,239
Leni, stop! Come on!

268
00:16:30,322 --> 00:16:36,578
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

269
00:16:39,039 --> 00:16:41,834
What's going on?
Is this a fire drill?

270
00:16:41,917 --> 00:16:43,711
- [LINE RINGING]
- They're not picking up.

271
00:16:43,794 --> 00:16:45,587
Fin, what's going on?

272
00:16:45,671 --> 00:16:47,548
Someone fired a gun near the commissary!

273
00:16:47,631 --> 00:16:48,590
What?!

274
00:16:48,674 --> 00:16:52,761
[ALARM BEEPING]

275
00:16:52,845 --> 00:16:54,763
[MAN] Let's go.

276
00:16:55,597 --> 00:16:56,849
Come on.

277
00:16:56,932 --> 00:17:03,188
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

278
00:17:05,065 --> 00:17:07,317
Doc, what's going on?

279
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:09,403
Is there a fire?

280
00:17:10,988 --> 00:17:13,073
Nurse, can you check
what's going on outside?

281
00:17:13,157 --> 00:17:15,325
- Yes, Doc. I'll check.
- Thank you.

282
00:17:15,409 --> 00:17:21,081
- [ALARM BEEPING]
- [DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

283
00:17:31,175 --> 00:17:34,636
We can't let Liam call the cops.

284
00:17:35,387 --> 00:17:36,472
Pa.

285
00:17:36,555 --> 00:17:38,640
Leni! Why'd you come back?

286
00:17:39,433 --> 00:17:41,060
Pa, I'm begging you.

287
00:17:41,143 --> 00:17:43,103
Stop this.

288
00:17:43,187 --> 00:17:45,981
- What happened?
- She suddenly got out of the truck.

289
00:17:46,982 --> 00:17:48,442
Put her in the wheelchair.

290
00:17:49,526 --> 00:17:50,694
Assist her!

291
00:17:52,863 --> 00:17:55,991
Boss, we can't stay here any longer.
We need to go inside now.

292
00:17:59,036 --> 00:18:00,412
Nurse?

293
00:18:00,496 --> 00:18:01,914
What's going on outside?

294
00:18:01,997 --> 00:18:05,709
Wait, sir. I'll just finish
her immunotherapy.

295
00:18:05,793 --> 00:18:08,879
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

296
00:18:08,962 --> 00:18:10,839
I'll go check now, sir. Excuse me.

297
00:18:10,923 --> 00:18:11,924
Thank you.

298
00:18:14,676 --> 00:18:17,221
Are we going to be fine, Daddy?

299
00:18:18,388 --> 00:18:20,432
[SIGHS] Yes, dear.

300
00:18:20,516 --> 00:18:21,975
We're gonna be fine.

301
00:18:22,059 --> 00:18:28,857
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

302
00:18:32,277 --> 00:18:37,825
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

303
00:18:37,908 --> 00:18:39,326
- [GUNSHOT]
- [YELPS]

304
00:18:39,409 --> 00:18:40,661
[PEOPLE CLAMORING]

305
00:18:40,744 --> 00:18:43,372
[GUNSHOTS]

306
00:18:43,455 --> 00:18:45,082
- [GRUNTING]
- [GUNSHOT]

307
00:18:47,042 --> 00:18:48,836
- [GRUNTS]
- [GUNSHOT]

308
00:18:48,919 --> 00:18:51,755
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

309
00:18:51,839 --> 00:18:53,257
- [GUNSHOT]
- [GRUNTS]

310
00:19:02,558 --> 00:19:04,810
<i>What's going on?</i>
<i>Is this a fire drill?</i>

311
00:19:04,893 --> 00:19:06,019
<i>We need to leave now, Ma.</i>

312
00:19:06,103 --> 00:19:09,773
- [GUNSHOT]
- [PEOPLE CLAMORING]

313
00:19:09,857 --> 00:19:11,650
[EMIL] <i>The police are aware of us now.</i>

314
00:19:11,733 --> 00:19:13,443
[COP] <i>Hey, where are you going?!</i>
<i>Over here!</i>

315
00:19:13,527 --> 00:19:15,863
<i>Get to the senator's son.</i>

316
00:19:17,489 --> 00:19:18,574
- [GRETA] <i>Liam!</i>
<i>- Ma!</i>

317
00:19:18,657 --> 00:19:20,325
<i>- I've been looking for you.</i>
<i>- We need to go.</i>

318
00:19:20,409 --> 00:19:21,952
<i>Why? What's going on?</i>

319
00:19:22,035 --> 00:19:23,829
<i>Emil Padua and his men are alive.</i>

320
00:19:23,912 --> 00:19:25,831
- <i>They're here at the hospital.</i>
- [GUNSHOTS]

321
00:19:26,456 --> 00:19:28,917
<i>Son, someone's shooting people back there!</i>

322
00:19:29,543 --> 00:19:31,753
<i>What matters is we get out of here, okay?</i>

323
00:19:34,047 --> 00:19:35,883
<i>You made things harder for me.</i>

324
00:19:35,966 --> 00:19:38,218
[GRUNTING]

325
00:19:38,302 --> 00:19:39,553
<i>Stay back!</i>

326
00:19:40,679 --> 00:19:42,139
<i>Or we'll all explode!</i>

327
00:19:48,478 --> 00:19:49,813
[GRUNTS]

328
00:19:50,439 --> 00:19:53,442
- [OLSEN YELLS]
- [EXPLOSION]

329
00:19:55,068 --> 00:19:57,112
[GRUNTING, GROANING]

330
00:19:57,196 --> 00:19:59,740
[REPORTER] <i>It has been confirmed</i>
<i>that the hostage takers</i>

331
00:19:59,823 --> 00:20:02,242
<i>have Senator Eduardo Maristella,</i>
<i>Macky Maristella,</i>

332
00:20:02,326 --> 00:20:05,037
<i>Greta Roja, and her son, Liam Roja.</i>

333
00:20:05,829 --> 00:20:06,830
<i>Olsen!</i>

334
00:20:06,914 --> 00:20:08,624
<i>Wendy, Emil has a big grudge against me.</i>

335
00:20:08,707 --> 00:20:12,169
<i>If something happens to Olsen,</i>
<i>it would be because of you?!</i>

336
00:20:12,252 --> 00:20:14,254
<i>I treat Olsen like my own kid.</i>

337
00:20:14,338 --> 00:20:17,507
<i>There's a possibility that he's my son.</i>
<i>Be honest with me!</i>

338
00:20:17,591 --> 00:20:19,676
[DADO] <i>Don't try to remove that.</i>

339
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:22,721
<i>If you get more than 50 meters away,</i>
<i>this is what will happen to you.</i>

340
00:20:24,139 --> 00:20:27,893
- [EXPLOSION]
- [PEOPLE CLAMORING]

341
00:20:27,976 --> 00:20:29,937
<i>Do you think you can</i>
<i>get away with this again?</i>

342
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:31,980
<i>We will get away with this.</i>

343
00:20:34,191 --> 00:20:35,817
- [GUNSHOT]
- [GRUNTS]

344
00:20:36,860 --> 00:20:38,737
[MINNIE] <i>Where will we pass through?</i>

345
00:20:40,781 --> 00:20:44,284
[EMIL] <i>Which of your two sons</i>
<i>are you going to choose to save,</i>

346
00:20:44,368 --> 00:20:47,120
<i>and which one will you leave to die?</i>

347
00:20:47,204 --> 00:20:48,830
<i>If you won't choose,</i>

348
00:20:48,914 --> 00:20:51,291
<i>I'll push them both.</i>
